<br>
1. A Mob that can Rampage has 2 agro lists.  The first agro list is the Hate list.  You want your main tank on top here..  The other agro list is the Rampage list.  The Rampage list is the list of players in the order in which the mob got mad at them.<br>
<br>
2. Luclin level mobs and below, once on Rampage list, you are forever on that mobs rampage list. If you die, zone, come back to the mob in 3 days, you will still be on the rampage list in the same spot. You can never go up or down the list unless someone before you scores a mem wipe (monk/SK FD can wipe them off rampage list)  There are two ways to clear rampage.  1. Kill the mob, 2 Memwipe the mob (enchanter wipes everyone or Monk and SK can Feign Death and wipe themselves).   This makes it very easy to set up rampage tanks, as mob is being pulled to camp, have MT, SA, other rampage tanks shoot arrows at the mob.  Its even easier on perma rooted mobs. Debuff/Slow mob with enchanter/shammy/mage and then have enchanter mem blur and then have MT, SA and as how ever many back up rampage tanks you want shoot arrows in the order you want them to take rampage.  This keeps your monks/rogues, casters and most important clerics off rampage list.<br>
<br>
3. Can not hide from rampage.  If you are in range (range on some mobs is very small, others huge) you will get hit, Mobs can Hit, Kick, Bash, Proc on Rampage.  If you are behind a wall, but in range you will get hit, if you are behind mob, you will get hit.  If you are out of range then the rampage will pass down to next available person on list.<br>
<br>
4. In Pop it appears they did Rampage a little different.  Haven't quite figured it out myself, but its strange...  <br>
<br>
Example of PoP:  Pulling POS mini, on the way in, MT and ST and one other rampage tank shoot arrows at the mob as its INC.  Mob gets to group, monk FD, MT engages calls assist, I cast nuke, mob rampages.. I take the rampage...gah next rampage not me but I still in range...<br>
<br>
<br>
edit: one other thing is your main tank (person on top of the hate list, you hope) will never get rampaged. <p><BR>
